# Generated parser output
# The parse-user-guide.js script produces a large JSON file (approximately
# 14–20 MB with default settings; see README for details).
# It is intentionally excluded from the repository by default so it is not
# accidentally committed. The user should run the parser locally and then
# either:
#   a) remove or override this rule (comment out or delete the line below)
#      and commit the generated file when they are ready to upload it, or
#   b) host the file separately and reference it via URL in index.html.
#
# To commit the generated output, simply remove the matching line(s) below
# or add a forced-include rule in your own .git/info/exclude or local config:
#   git add -f data/cohesity-user-guide-knowledge.json
data/cohesity-user-guide-knowledge.json
data/cohesity-user-guide-knowledge.jsonl

# Temporary/scratch outputs from the parser (always ignored)
data/*.tmp.json
data/*.tmp.jsonl
